1
00:00:04,298 --> 00:00:08,341
It’s all … it’s a dream, 
this whole world.

2
00:00:08,341 --> 00:00:12,382
So, good dream, bad dream, 
is a dream;

3
00:00:12,382 --> 00:00:14,714
there’s nothing substantial there.

4
00:00:14,946 --> 00:00:18,021
[Counterfeit Reality]

5
00:00:18,145 --> 00:00:21,277
So Guru Mahārāj 
likes to remind us,

6
00:00:21,277 --> 00:00:23,053
like we might see at times,

7
00:00:23,053 --> 00:00:26,561
the moon, 
in the rainy season

8
00:00:26,561 --> 00:00:30,862
when the moon 
is covered by clouds,

9
00:00:30,862 --> 00:00:39,262
all you see 
is an illumined cloud;

10
00:00:39,262 --> 00:00:44,780
but what’s illuminating the cloud 
is the moon behind it—

11
00:00:46,980 --> 00:00:51,317
the cloud has no illumination 
on its own.

12
00:00:51,317 --> 00:00:53,011
So what is the cloud?

13
00:00:53,011 --> 00:00:58,800
Mind, intelligence, ego.

14
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:01,340
Just like that cloud 
that’s covering the moon,

15
00:01:01,340 --> 00:01:03,926
they’re covering this body.

16
00:01:03,926 --> 00:01:07,753
The senses, the body, mind, 
intelligence, and ego.

17
00:01:07,753 --> 00:01:10,222
These layers, they’re like clouds
covering the soul;

18
00:01:10,222 --> 00:01:12,816
it’s the soul 
that’s illuminating them.

19
00:01:12,816 --> 00:01:16,268
So when we look at somebody 
they’ll look like they’re alive,

20
00:01:16,775 --> 00:01:19,980
or they’ll look like 
they’re thinking,

21
00:01:19,980 --> 00:01:23,339
or they’re doing 
so many things;

22
00:01:23,339 --> 00:01:29,461
actually it’s the soul 
who’s the doer in the background.

23
00:01:29,461 --> 00:01:37,687
So we need to go first 
to the soul plane—

24
00:01:40,209 --> 00:01:45,588
everything else is a covering; 
an acquired prejudice;

25
00:01:45,588 --> 00:01:48,980
a misreading.

26
00:01:48,980 --> 00:01:53,540
Only someone who is in 
pure Kṛṣṇa consciousness

27
00:01:53,540 --> 00:02:02,260
can read the environment and
environmental circumstances properly.

28
00:02:05,167 --> 00:02:07,304
Like an instrument,

29
00:02:08,381 --> 00:02:12,286
we need to be recalibrated.

30
00:02:12,532 --> 00:02:14,837
Sādhu, Śāstra. 
Guru, Vaiṣṇava.

31
00:02:14,837 --> 00:02:20,305
Recalibrated. Then you can begin
to read properly,

32
00:02:20,782 --> 00:02:23,942
and on the basis 
of proper readings,

33
00:02:23,942 --> 00:02:25,143
proceed.

34
00:02:25,143 --> 00:02:28,505
Without being recalibrated, 
all the readings are false,

35
00:02:28,505 --> 00:02:32,216
and we’re making so many 
important decisions

36
00:02:32,216 --> 00:02:34,781
about doing this, not doing that, 
going this way …

37
00:02:34,781 --> 00:02:40,422
But the compass is off;

38
00:02:40,422 --> 00:02:45,100
the instrument is giving 
false readings.

39
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:47,861
That’s what ahaṅkāra does: 
gives a false reading

40
00:02:47,861 --> 00:02:51,903
of who I am; what is life; 
what are life’s circumstances;

41
00:02:51,903 --> 00:02:58,818
how I should proceed on the basis 
of that misconceived self and identity.

42
00:02:59,298 --> 00:03:03,700
Like the old Russian joke 
about the three crazy guys

43
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:06,920
in the nuthouse talking to each other,

44
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:10,020
and one said, “God told me …”,

45
00:03:10,020 --> 00:03:13,942
and the other one goes, “No, no, 
God told me just the opposite of that!”,

46
00:03:13,942 --> 00:03:16,091
and the third guy says,

47
00:03:16,091 --> 00:03:19,718
“I never told either one of you 
either one of those things.”

48
00:03:19,718 --> 00:03:24,159
He’s crazier than 
the other two guys.

49
00:03:28,143 --> 00:03:31,026
That’s what 
we’re dealing with—

50
00:03:31,026 --> 00:03:33,150
people are going to think 
God told them this,

51
00:03:33,150 --> 00:03:36,962
or, “I never said that”, and …

52
00:03:38,346 --> 00:03:43,218
Really, that’s 
what’s going on.

53
00:03:48,018 --> 00:03:54,002
So, first, locate the self; 
locate ātmā, first.

54
00:03:54,341 --> 00:03:57,344
That’s the beginning.

55
00:03:58,145 --> 00:04:02,085
But just to try
and recondition the mundane:

56
00:04:02,085 --> 00:04:04,011
that’s not a spiritual project;

57
00:04:04,011 --> 00:04:05,943
these are all mundane things.

58
00:04:05,943 --> 00:04:09,095
So, just to recondition mind:

59
00:04:09,095 --> 00:04:12,871
that’s not Kṛṣṇa consciousness; 
you won’t get any—.

60
00:04:12,871 --> 00:04:16,785
That’s prākṛta sahajiyā-ism; 
that’s their idea—

61
00:04:17,741 --> 00:04:23,625
neuro-linguistic programming 
for the mind and the intelligence.

62
00:04:23,918 --> 00:04:37,692
All you will get is simulated, 
superficial, counterfeit reality.

63
00:04:37,780 --> 00:04:46,032
There’s one gopī 
who’s taking bel fruit

64
00:04:46,032 --> 00:04:48,459
—have you ever seen bel fruits?—

65
00:04:48,459 --> 00:04:57,541
taking bel fruit and putting them 
in her … what do you call it?

66
00:04:57,541 --> 00:05:00,690
Like, ‘choli’; in her blouse,

67
00:05:00,690 --> 00:05:02,990
thinking that … And the others going,

68
00:05:02,990 --> 00:05:04,908
“Oh, we should watch out 
for this one—

69
00:05:04,908 --> 00:05:08,542
she’s really going to attract Kṛṣṇa.”

70
00:05:08,542 --> 00:05:11,301
I mean, it’s a Rūpa Goswāmī śloka,

71
00:05:11,301 --> 00:05:14,870
… says she’s putting bel fruit.

